      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Siding with Victorian visitor SMOKEN ACE NZ (3) first up. He put together a string of wins last time in including the Listed Popular Alm at Kilmore. Gets a good draw and has recorded a win and a placing in two tries at the mile. Proven fresh and should be ready to go off a nice trial. HUTA NZ (11) put the writing on the wall when runner-up two back before delivering last week, leading to score by 4m at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but could go on with it now that he has broken through. RIPP (10) continued his consistent form when he raced parked from this barrier but stuck on for second last week. Reliable and could return to the winners' list. GLITTER AINT GOLD (1) came from wider to place last week and won two of his previous three outings here, one at Listed level. Prefer him over further but should get every chance from the ace draw.",
